File "static.php", line 4, characters 28-39:
The closest thing is staticMethod but it's a static method

      In PHP, static methods can be called at the class level or the instance level. For example, the following two ways to call bar() are both acceptable:



<?php
class Foo {
  public static function bar() {
    echo "Hello";
  }
}

// Instance level
$f = new Foo();
$f::bar();

// Class level
Foo::bar();

      Hack does not allow the instance level static calls in // strict mode (this is allowed in // partial mode). Hack will balk about using "dynamic classes".



<?hh // strict
class Foo {
  public static function bar() {
    echo "Hello";
  }
}

function main_csm() {
  // Instance level
  $f = new Foo();
  // Hack will balk here
  $f::bar();

  // Class level
  Foo::bar();
}

main_csm();


